text: Winkler County is a county in the state of Texas in the United States. In 2020, 7,791 people lived there. The county seat is Kermit. It is named for Clinton M. Winkler, a Colonel in the Confederate Army. Music maker Roy Orbison completed High School in Winkler County. == History == Winkler County was created in 1887 and set up in 1910. == Geography == The county has a total area of 841 square miles. == Places == === Cities === * Kermit (county seat) * Wink == References == Category:Texas counties
title: Winkler County, Texas
